}\n\n{{2010\u20132019 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Satta, Melissa}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Sardinian descent]]\n[[Category:American showgirls]]\n[[Category:Communication scholars]]\n[[Category:American television hosts]]\n[[Category:American women in business]]\n[[Category:University of Milan alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Boston]]\n[[Category:People from Cagliari]]\n[[Category:Footballers' wives and girlfriends]]\n[[Category:Women television presenters]]\n[[Category:American karateka]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian television presenter}}\t\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name          = Melissa Satta\n| image         = Melissa Satta (cropped).jpg\n| caption       = Satta in May 2007\n| birth_name    =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1986|2|07}}<ref name=\"nuova_sardegna_ledda\">{{cite news |title=Sarda la bruna, brasiliana la bionda. Ecco le nuove veline|url=http://ricerca.gelocal.it/lanuovasardegna/archivio/lanuovasardegna/2005/09/24/ST9SD_ST901.html|author=Marco Ledda|location=Sassari|magazine=[[La Nuova Sardegna]]|date=24 September 2005|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_place   = [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], U.S.\n| alma_mater    = [[IULM University of Milan]]\n| partner       = {{plainlist|\n*[[:it:Daniele Interrante|Daniele Interrante]] (2003\u20132006)\n*[[Christian Vieri]] (2006\u20132011)\n}}\n| spouse        = {{marriage|[[Kevin-Prince Boateng]]|2016}}\n| children      = 1\n| height        = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| haircolor     = Brown\n| eyecolor      = Green\n| citizenship   = [[United States nationality law|American]] and [[Italian nationality law|Italian]]  <!-- Italian law: if one of your parents you've got italian citizenship as well -->\n| agency        = \n| occupation    = {{flatlist|\n*television presenter\n}}\n|yearsactive    = 2002\u2013present\n| website       = {{url|http://www.melissasatta.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Melissa Satta''' (born 7 February 1986<ref name=\"nuova_sardegna_ledda\"/>) is an Italian [[television presenter]]. She was a [[showgirl]] in the Italian satirical series ''[[Striscia la notizia]]''. Satta has appeared in ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine and was featured in the 2010 [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit issue]]. Satta lives and works in Italy.<ref>{{fashionmodel|Melissa_Satta|Melissa Satta}}</ref><ref>[http://www.direttanews.it/2010/06/11/melissa-satta-in-bikini-su-maxim/ Melissa Satta in bikini su Maxim] (Italian)</ref><ref>[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/swimsuit/modelfeatured/melissa_satta/2010/body_painting/index.htm Melissa Satta's bodypaint shoot for the 2010 ''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit issue].</ref>\n\n==Early years==\nSatta was born to [[Italians|Italian]] parents, native to the island of [[Sardinia]], Mariangela Muzzu and Enzo Satta, on 7 February 1986 in [[Boston]], Massachusetts, United States.<ref name=\"dpboss\">{{Cite web|url=https://ricerca.gelocal.it/lanuovasardegna/archivio/lanuovasardegna/2005/09/24/ST9SD_ST901.html?refresh_ce |title=No title |last=Ledda |first=Marco |date=24 September 2005 |website=lanuovasardegna.it |publisher=[[La Nuova Sardegna]] |access-date=8 April 2020 |language=Italian}}</ref> She spent the early years of her childhood living both in the U.S. and in Sardinia.<ref name=\"dpboss\"/> Satta's father, Enzo Satta, is an [[architect]] and he was a Sardinian [[Local government|government]] and [[central government]] [[politician]] in [[politics of Sardinia]] and [[Political consulting|political consultant]] and [[business partner]] to [[Aga Khan IV|Prince Aga Khan IV]] from 1986 until 2003, in which he [[Representation (politics)|politically represented]] [[Costa Smeralda]] in Sardinia and was responsible for the [[architectural planning]] of Costa Smeralda.<ref name=\"dpboss\"/><ref name=\"Online Satta - AskMen\"/><ref>[http://www.satta.com/profilo.htm site architect Enzo Satta]</ref> Satta has two brothers; an older brother, Riccardo, a [[business incubator]] and entrepreneur resident in the [[Principality of Monaco]], and a younger brother, Maximilian.<ref name=\"Satta's brother in trouble with the IRS\">{{cite news | date= 21 November 2007 | url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/07_novembre_21/Satta_evasione_fiscale_ec3e2b52-9813-11dc-89d7-0003ba99c53b.shtml | title= Il fratello della Satta nei guai con il fisco|trans-title=<!--Satta's brother in trouble with the IRS-->| last=|first=| work=corriere.it|publisher=[[Corriere della Sera]]| accessdate= 27 December 2011| language = Italian}}</ref><ref>[http://www.l-camillo.com/Camillo/Cam-17.htm The Satta-Bacciu Story].www.l-camillo.com. Retrieved 27 December 2011.</ref> After graduating from [[high school]] in the United States, Satta enrolled in the faculty of [[Communication studies]] at the [[private university]] IULM, but there is no evidence of the achievement of the diploma and the end of her studies.<ref name=\"dpboss\"/><ref name=\"Online Satta - AskMen\">{{cite news| date=| url=http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/women/models_400/419_melissa_satta.html| title=Online Satta - AskMen| trans-title=| last=| first=| work=askmen.com| publisher=[[AskMen.com]]| accessdate=14 December 2011| language=| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108051526/http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/women/models_400/419_melissa_satta.html| archive-date=8 January 2012| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nSatta has a history of sports, having practiced both [[Women's association football|women's football]], which she played with the women's team of Sardinian Sant'Elena Quartu, and [[karate]], winning the Sardinian Junior Karate Championships and a national junior [[bronze medal]].<ref name=\"dpboss\"/><ref name=\"Online Satta - AskMen\"/>\n\n==Career==\nSatta began working in the fashion industry at age 16 in 2002. In 2003 she was among the finalists of the [[beauty contest]] ''Miss wall'' (edition 2003) and obtained the title of ''Miss extreme''.{{citation needed|date=March 2016}} In 2005, she began working as a presenter in the Italian television program ''Mio fratello \u00e8 Pakistano'', which was starred by presenter [[:it:Teo Mammucari|Teo Mammucari]] on [[Canale 5]]. In the same year she was appointed as [[spokesperson]] for the advertising of [[Telecom Italia Mobile|TIM]].<ref name=\"cerv\">[http://www.portocervo. net / modules.php? name = News & file = article & sid = 250 Sarda the brunette, the blonde Brazilian. Here are the new tissue]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, article in \"La Nuova Sardegna\" reported by site portocervo.net.</ref><ref name=\"Melissa Satta - AskMen\">{{cite news| date=| url=http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/women/models_400/419_melissa_satta.html| title=Melissa Satta - AskMen| trans-title=| last=| first=| work=askmen.com| publisher=[[AskMen.com]]| accessdate=14 December 2011| language=| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108051526/http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/women/models_400/419_melissa_satta.html| archive-date=8 January 2012| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nSatta appeared on the Italian television program ''[[Striscia la notizia]]'' from 2006 to 2008. In 2006, she featured in numerous [[Mediaset]] television programs, such as ''[[:it:Il giudice Mastrangelo|Judge Mastrangelo 2]]'' and had a minor part in the Italian movie ''[[:it:Bastardi|Bastardi]]''. In the fall of 2006, Satta paraded the [[Runway (fashion)|catwalks]] in [[Milan Fashion Week|Milan]]'s fashion spring / summer 2007 to the Pin Up Stars collection.<ref name=\"cerv\"/><ref name=\"Melissa Satta - AskMen\"/>\n\nIn the summer of 2007, she starred in the last part of the [[MTV Italy]] program ''[[Total Request Live (Italy)|Total Request Live]]'', along with [[Alessandro Cattelan]], and also presented on [[Fashion TV]] and the Italian ''The White Party Fashion TV satellite channel''.<ref name=\"Melissa Satta - AskMen\"/>\n\nIn the autumn of 2008, alongside [[:it:Teo Mammucari|Teo Mammucari]], Satta presented the Italian quiz-show ''[[:it:Primo e ultimo|First and last]]'', which was inspired by an [[England|English]] format of [[Endemol UK]] and was broadcast on [[Rai 1]] in Italy.<ref name=\"cerv\"/><ref name=\"Melissa Satta - AskMen\"/> In the beginning of 2009, Satta became advertising [[protagonist]] of the [[commercials]] of [[Peugeot 107]] ''Sweet Years'' and in September 2009, Satta replaced the Chilean [[Model (person)|model]] Maria Jose Lopez as the female face of the Italian talk show [[:it:Controcampo (programma televisivo)|Controcampo]] on [[Rete 4]].<ref name=\"cerv\"/> In 2009, Satta television presented for [[Victoria's Secret]].<ref name=\"Melissa Satta - AskMen\"/>\n\nIn February 2010, Satta featured in the magazine [[Sports Illustrated]] for the special issue dedicated to swimwear (''Sports Illustrated Magazine Swimsuit Issue'') for a [[photo shoot]] \"wearing\" a [[body painting]] representing the top of the Italy national football team.<ref>[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2010_swimsuit/painting/melissa- satta / Data on the service] at the [[Sports Illustrated]].</ref> Throughout 2010, Satta presented Italian television show ''[[:it:Episodio pilota|episodio pilota]]'' along with presenter [[:it:Platinette|Platinette]]; aired on [[Sky Italy]]. Also in 2010, Satta appeared on the June 2010 cover of ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''.<ref>[http://www.maxim.it/girls/article/maxim_girls_melissa_satta_-_golden_wag/ Melissa Satta article and photos on the official site of Maxim magazine] (in Italian). maxim.it. Retrieved 22 April 2013.</ref>\n\nIn June 2011, Satta lead presented the scientific program ''[[Insideout]] (Tutti pazzi per la scienza)''; aired on [[Rai 2]].<ref>[http://www.rai2.rai.it/dl/RaiDue/programma.html?ContentItem-1e50e17c-d942-4ad5-88fb-1d37dab14ab8 Insideout program (Tutti pazzi per la scienza)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111213044639/http://www.rai2.rai.it/dl/RaiDue/programma.html?ContentItem-1e50e17c-d942-4ad5-88fb-1d37dab14ab8 |date=13 December 2011 }} (in Italian). ''rai2.rai.it''. Retrieved 22 April 2013.</ref> In December 2011, she featured on talk show ''[[:it:Kalisp\u00e9ra!|Kalisp\u00e9ra!]]'' along with television presenters [[Pamela Prati]] and [[:it:Alfonso Signorini|Alfonso Signorini]]; aired on [[Canale 5]].<ref>[http://www.tv.mediaset.it/canale5/kalispera/program Kalisp\u00e9ra: the web site of Mediaset] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130616094914/http://www.tv.mediaset.it/canale5/kalispera/program |date=16 June 2013 }} (in Italian). ''tv.mediaset.it''. Retrieved 22 April 2013.</ref> Throughout 2011, Satta was selected as the [[testimonial]] and [[Advertising|commercials]] endorser of different multi-national brands such as [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] and [[Nicole Miller|Nicole]] (luxury fashion and jewelry company of [[Nicole Miller]]).<ref>[http://www.nicolespose.it/nicole2012/melissa-satta-per-nicole/collezione-nicole-spose.php Section of the site of Nicole Brides with photos of Melissa Satta testimonial] (in Italian). ''nicolespose.it''. Retrieved 22 April 2013.</ref>\n\nIn May 2012, Satta featured on television program ''[[:it:Punto su di te!|Punto su di te!]]'' presented with [[Elisa Isoardi]]; aired on [[Rai 1]]. Throughout 2012 and into 2013, Satta filmed episodes of ''Intitolata Amici a letto [[sitcom]]'' by [[Comedy Central Italy]] subdivision [[Comedy Central]].<ref>[http://www.comedycentral.it/shows/amici-a-letto/ Comedy Central official Page of friends in bed] (in Italian). ''comedycentral.it''. Retrieved 22 April 2013.</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, Satta and [[Rafael Ben\u00edtez]], the then [[Manager (association football)|manager]] of Italian giants [[S.S.C. Napoli]], were appointed as presenters of Italy [[Broadcasting of sports events|sports program]] ''TikiTaka'' on [[Italia 1]], [[Mediaset Italia]].<ref>[http://www.sportmediaset.mediaset.it/calcio/calcio/2013/articoli/1011717/-tiki-taka-con-rafa-benitez-e-melissa-satta.shtml.\"Tiki Taka\" con Rafa Benitez e Melissa Satta]{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} (in Italian). ''[[Mediaset Italia]] ([[Mediaset]])''. 22 September 2013.</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBetween 2003 and 2006, Satta was in a relationship with [[Italian people|Italian]] television personality [[:it:Daniele Interrante|Daniele Interrante]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/12/21/melissa-satta-la-mia-storia-con-daniele-interrante-povera-me-ero-una-bambina-e-lui-risponde-le-parole-della-signora-lo-trovo-scorretto-e-vergognoso/4852517/ |title=Melissa Satta: \u201cLa mia storia con Daniele Interrante? Povera me, ero una bambina\u201d. E lui risponde: \u201cLe parole della signora? Lo trovo scorretto e vergognoso\u201d |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |language=Italian |last1=Candela |first1=Giuseppe |date=21 December 2018 |accessdate=12 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\nBetween 2006 and 2011, Satta was in a relationship with Italian footballer [[Christian Vieri]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/televisione/speciale-amarcord/buon-compleanno-bobo-vieri-eccolo-vent-anni-fa-nella-sigla-di-mai-dire-gol-_3219780-201902a.shtml |title=Buon compleanno \"Bobo\" Vieri, eccolo vent\u02bcanni fa nella sigla di \"Mai Dire Gol\" |publisher=www.tgcom24.mediaset.it |language=Italian |date=12 July 2019 |accessdate=12 November 2019 }}</ref> In April 2011, their relationship ended because of his alleged [[infidelity]] with [[Sara Tommasi]].<ref name=\"Christian Vieri breaks up with girlfriend Melissa Satta\">{{cite news|url=http://www.blogdolcevita.com/post/4168/italian-football-player-christian-vieri-breaks-up-with-girlfriend-melissa-satta|title=Italian football player Christian Vieri breaks up with girlfriend Melissa Satta|work=dolcevita.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212125823/http://www.blogdolcevita.com/post/4168/italian-football-player-chri